    "notes": "G6.5V solar-twin (0.93 Msun, 0.987 Rsun, Teff 5568 K) at 8.534 pc with three RV-detected planets (b/c/d, Vogt 2010) and a Herschel-resolved cold debris belt at ~30-96 AU (Wyatt 2012). Phase 2 anchor is Rathsam et al. 2023 (lithium-depletion solar-analog isochrone) which supplies the smallest formal uncertainties on mass, Teff, [Fe/H], and age. Radius primary is von Braun 2014 CHARA interferometry (R = 0.9867 +/- 0.0048 Rsun) — supersedes the Vogt 2010 evolutionary radius (0.963 +/- 0.011) which earlier Phase 3 drafts incorrectly labeled 'interferometric angular diameter combined with parallax'; Vogt 2010 actually derives R from Takeda 2007 isochrone analysis. Age is contentious: isochrone consensus (Rathsam 2023 / Vogt 2010 / von Braun 2014) gives 7.7-9 Gyr while activity-age (Mamajek 2008) gives 6.1 +/- 1.7 Gyr — Phase 3 adopts the isochrone value but flags Confidence=medium. Rotation P_rot = 32.1 +/- 0.2 d is Yu 2024's direct Gaussian-process detection from 18-year HARPS RV+activity time series, replacing the earlier inferred ~29 d from Wright 2004 S-index variation. log R'HK = -5.0 (Isaacson 2010 / Henry 1996) places 61 Vir firmly in the inactive G-dwarf locus, consistent with the ~8 Gyr isochrone age."
